1
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:06,600
Yeah.

2
00:00:06,950 --> 00:00:07,950
What do you think?

3
00:00:10,160 --> 00:00:11,160
They look great on you.

4
00:00:11,700 --> 00:00:12,700
You too, Natsume-san.

5
00:00:14,170 --> 00:00:16,090
I wouldn't actually mind
getting my ears pierced.

6
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:18,490
In fact, if I do it,
I'd want you to be the one to do it.

7
00:00:18,810 --> 00:00:20,550
Give me a break.

8
00:00:21,100 --> 00:00:22,100
I told you already,

9
00:00:22,140 --> 00:00:23,670
go to a clinic if you want piercings.

10
00:00:24,930 --> 00:00:26,290
But I'm happy.

11
00:00:26,710 --> 00:00:29,150
It feels like I'm taking a piece of you
with me wherever I go.

12
00:00:30,670 --> 00:00:31,670
Is that so?

13
00:00:32,690 --> 00:00:33,890
I'm glad, then.

14
00:00:40,580 --> 00:00:41,950
Wait, is it a ring?

15
00:00:43,580 --> 00:00:44,780
Is this the moment?

16
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:48,640
Alright.

17
00:00:48,641 --> 00:00:49,890
Let's get to work.

18
00:00:54,710 --> 00:00:55,710
Oh...

19
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:58,360
Seriously?

20
00:00:59,090 --> 00:01:00,190
I guess I was wrong.

21
00:01:57,500 --> 00:02:01,500
"Cosmetic Playlover Season 2"
(Episode 10)

22
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:04,969
Welcome! Are you looking
for anything in particular today?

23
00:02:04,970 --> 00:02:05,650
I'd like to look at some lipsticks.

24
00:02:05,651 --> 00:02:07,300
Of course. Right this way, please.

25
00:02:10,200 --> 00:02:11,590
Now that it's March,

26
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,500
all ROMY branches

27
00:02:13,950 --> 00:02:16,870
are holding our limited-time
Spring Campaign.

28
00:02:20,100 --> 00:02:21,539
Since the seasons are changing,

29
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:24,050
I'll include some eye
cream samples for you.

30
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:25,310
Thank you.

31
00:02:25,740 --> 00:02:26,590
Of course.

32
00:02:26,591 --> 00:02:29,430
I've actually been worried
about my eye area lately.

33
00:02:29,530 --> 00:02:30,180
Oh, really?

34
00:02:30,181 --> 00:02:32,010
Hoshina-kun, who used to be a rookie,

35
00:02:32,500 --> 00:02:33,700
has completely settled in now.

36
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,730
He seems to enjoy his work every day.

37
00:02:41,270 --> 00:02:43,150
Welcome!

38
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:44,369
I was just in the neighborhood,

39
00:02:44,370 --> 00:02:46,160
so I thought I'd pick up Fruy #5.

40
00:02:46,402 --> 00:02:48,062
Plus, I wanted to see you, Mamiya-san.

41
00:02:48,420 --> 00:02:50,450
Thank you so much.

42
00:02:54,110 --> 00:02:56,070
This is the shade you wanted, right?

43
00:02:56,460 --> 00:02:57,460
Yes, that's it.

44
00:02:57,780 --> 00:02:59,100
I'll get that wrapped up for you.

45
00:03:00,980 --> 00:03:02,610
I'm glad it's still in stock.

46
00:03:03,340 --> 00:03:05,330
I'm going to London for a month next month,

47
00:03:05,420 --> 00:03:06,980
leaving my husband all by himself here.

48
00:03:07,050 --> 00:03:08,090
I see.

49
00:03:08,860 --> 00:03:12,590
But then he's going to New York
on business the month after that.

50
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:15,440
So you'll just keep missing each other?

51
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:17,080
Exactly.

52
00:03:17,570 --> 00:03:20,840
It's hard to spend time together,
even though we're married.

53
00:03:22,480 --> 00:03:23,480
Ah.

54
00:03:24,020 --> 00:03:25,020
Wait, no.

55
00:03:25,860 --> 00:03:28,110
Maybe it's because it's so hard
to be together

56
00:03:28,540 --> 00:03:29,930
that we decided to get married.

57
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,960
"Because we're apart so much,

58
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,080
that's why we got married?"

59
00:03:35,370 --> 00:03:36,370
That's right.

60
00:03:37,660 --> 00:03:39,210
I think we both

61
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:42,490
just wanted that commitment.

62
00:03:44,270 --> 00:03:45,740
Even when we're apart,

63
00:03:46,410 --> 00:03:48,849
I can keep going knowing it's a reward
for the next time we meet.

64
00:03:48,850 --> 00:03:50,040
I can work hard for that.

65
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:55,000
It makes our time together
feel that much more special.

66
00:03:57,300 --> 00:03:58,300
Don't you think?

67
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:22,820
Can I feel that way too?

68
00:04:24,060 --> 00:04:25,790
Even after Touma leaves for Paris?

69
00:04:51,010 --> 00:04:52,290
Alright, all done.

70
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,100
Thanks.

71
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:55,840
Left hand.

72
00:04:57,280 --> 00:04:59,030
When I'm finished, I'll do yours too.

73
00:04:59,420 --> 00:05:00,420
Thank you.

74
00:05:02,320 --> 00:05:04,590
Your hands get dry so easily, Natsume-san.

75
00:05:05,150 --> 00:05:07,390
You have to keep up with the moisturizing
while I'm gone.

76
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:09,000
Yeah, I know.

77
00:05:11,200 --> 00:05:12,200
Ah.

78
00:05:14,690 --> 00:05:15,690
By the way...

79
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:20,310
Is it a ring?

80
00:05:27,830 --> 00:05:28,830
Hand cream.

81
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:31,080
I got some samples of a new product.

82
00:05:31,340 --> 00:05:32,650
I'll put some on you in a bit.

83
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:34,820
Thanks.

84
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:38,040
Seriously...

85
00:05:44,970 --> 00:05:46,070
This guy...

86
00:05:47,030 --> 00:05:49,440
When is he ever going to give me that ring?

87
00:05:50,510 --> 00:05:52,149
Is he just watching me wait

88
00:05:52,150 --> 00:05:53,310
because he thinks it's funny?

89
00:05:59,320 --> 00:06:00,520
Can't sleep?

90
00:06:01,020 --> 00:06:02,910
No, I'm sleeping.

91
00:06:03,420 --> 00:06:04,520
I'm sleeping just fine.

92
00:06:15,630 --> 00:06:17,570
Man, what's wrong with me?

93
00:06:18,330 --> 00:06:19,970
I'm such a nervous wreck.

94
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,040
Huh?

95
00:06:30,065 --> 00:06:31,535
New recruit training?

96
00:06:32,190 --> 00:06:36,500
Yes, we have a lot of new hires this year.

97
00:06:37,086 --> 00:06:38,195
There are quite a few men in the group,

98
00:06:38,220 --> 00:06:39,980
so I'd really like you
to lead them, Mamiya.

99
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:41,939
I know you're already busy enough

100
00:06:41,940 --> 00:06:44,120
managing everything at the store as Chief.

101
00:06:44,510 --> 00:06:46,550
But can I count on you?

102
00:06:49,150 --> 00:06:51,050
The atmosphere at the store is great.

103
00:06:52,000 --> 00:06:54,010
Everyone takes initiative on their own.

104
00:06:55,390 --> 00:06:57,220
And Hoshina-kun is already a key player.

105
00:06:58,790 --> 00:06:59,790
So right now...

106
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:01,980
Sure.

107
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,549
If there's anything I can do to help,

108
00:07:03,550 --> 00:07:04,550
I'd be happy to.

109
00:07:05,340 --> 00:07:07,220
Then I'll leave it to
you starting next week.

110
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,040
Understood.

111
00:07:09,880 --> 00:07:10,880
And so,

112
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:13,260
the day of Touma's departure for Paris

113
00:07:13,670 --> 00:07:15,100
drew closer and closer.

114
00:07:15,643 --> 00:07:16,643
Wow.

115
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:19,380
We've had a non-stop stream
of customers this week.

116
00:07:20,170 --> 00:07:21,170
Hey, Sahashi-kun.

117
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:23,379
Want to grab lunch somewhere today?

118
00:07:23,380 --> 00:07:25,360
No thanks, I'll just eat here.

119
00:07:26,100 --> 00:07:27,300
Oh, come on.

120
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,929
You're leaving for Paris soon.

121
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:32,110
I just wanted to make some memories
before you go.

122
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:34,030
I'm fine.

123
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:38,220
You're the same as ever.
Nothing rattles you, does it?

124
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:40,600
Ah.

125
00:07:41,070 --> 00:07:42,230
Speaking of memories,

126
00:07:43,470 --> 00:07:44,860
I heard the news.

127
00:07:45,276 --> 00:07:47,060
Was that your idea, Sahashi-kun?

128
00:07:49,280 --> 00:07:50,770
What are you referring to?

129
00:07:56,050 --> 00:07:58,080
The training session was fantastic.

130
00:07:58,290 --> 00:08:02,080
The recruits were hanging
on your every word.

131
00:08:02,890 --> 00:08:05,520
I think you gave them all
something to aim for.

132
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,339
Thank you for doing this while
you're so busy, Mamiya-kun.

133
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:09,340
Oh, it was nothing.

134
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:12,180
I have a team I can really rely on
back at the store.

135
00:08:12,460 --> 00:08:14,020
Hoshina-kun has been working hard, too.

136
00:08:14,280 --> 00:08:15,280
Hearing that

137
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:18,160
makes me want to scout you
as a training instructor even more.

138
00:08:19,820 --> 00:08:20,860
Mamiya-kun,

139
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:22,760
I really think you'd be a natural at it.

140
00:08:23,950 --> 00:08:24,950
Well...

141
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:28,860
I do want to use my experience
to help others,

142
00:08:29,570 --> 00:08:30,770
but right now...

143
00:08:31,100 --> 00:08:32,100
I know.

144
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,190
Chief Mamiya on the front lines

145
00:08:34,260 --> 00:08:35,800
is a vital asset to ROMY.

146
00:08:36,910 --> 00:08:38,070
I'm talking about the future.

147
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:40,020
Just keep it in mind.

148
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,880
Okay.

149
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:42,980
I will.

150
00:08:43,190 --> 00:08:45,550
Ah, I have a meeting to get to.

151
00:08:45,780 --> 00:08:47,300
Give my best to everyone at the store.

152
00:08:47,470 --> 00:08:49,280
- See you later.
- Good work today.

153
00:08:52,610 --> 00:08:53,610
Natsume-kun!

154
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,770
- Tanouchi-san.
- Perfect timing.

155
00:08:56,890 --> 00:08:58,330
I was just about to call you.

156
00:08:58,740 --> 00:08:59,740
Huh?

157
00:09:01,360 --> 00:09:02,360
Wait...

158
00:09:02,730 --> 00:09:04,130
Sahashi-kun is coming to our store?

159
00:09:04,370 --> 00:09:05,370
That's right.

160
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:06,900
It's only for one day,

161
00:09:06,960 --> 00:09:09,000
on the final day of the Spring Campaign.

162
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,370
I've heard about it.

163
00:09:10,410 --> 00:09:11,930
The "Twin Princes of Yurakucho."

164
00:09:12,050 --> 00:09:14,640
Corporate really knows how to come up
with these flashy promos.

165
00:09:15,010 --> 00:09:17,820
This must be a send-off for Sahashi-kun
before he leaves for Paris.

166
00:09:17,930 --> 00:09:20,190
- The customers are going to love it.
- Yeah.

167
00:09:21,310 --> 00:09:22,939
The Twin Princes, together again.

168
00:09:22,940 --> 00:09:26,460
I get to work at the counter
with Touma one more time.

169
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:35,700
Yeah.

170
00:09:36,290 --> 00:09:37,370
So that's what's happening.

171
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:38,650
You hadn't heard?

172
00:09:38,651 --> 00:09:40,331
- No, I heard.
- What's with that reaction?

173
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,240
I'm really looking forward to it, though.

174
00:09:45,700 --> 00:09:47,220
Working at the counter together again.

175
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:49,560
Yeah.

176
00:09:50,160 --> 00:09:50,830
I'll do my best

177
00:09:50,831 --> 00:09:52,790
to be of help to you, Chief Mamiya.

178
00:09:54,060 --> 00:09:55,060
Sounds good.

179
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:02,960
And so,

180
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:06,000
Touma's preparations for Paris continued,

181
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:10,140
and yet, I still haven't gotten
that ring from him.

182
00:10:11,350 --> 00:10:14,550
And just like that, it's the morning
of the final day of the Spring Campaign.

183
00:10:25,580 --> 00:10:27,140
Sorry to keep you waiting, Natsume-san.

184
00:10:27,900 --> 00:10:29,000
Shall we go?

185
00:10:29,010 --> 00:10:30,010
Let's do it.

186
00:10:40,870 --> 00:10:44,550
Wow, this brings back memories.

187
00:10:45,800 --> 00:10:49,090
- They really do look right together, don't they?
- They really do.

188
00:10:49,710 --> 00:10:51,390
We won't see this for a while,

189
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:53,240
so I'm going to soak it all in.

190
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:55,050
So that's Sahashi Touma.

191
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:57,300
What an aura.

192
00:10:58,660 --> 00:11:02,010
I can see why they call them
the "Twin Princes."

193
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:06,730
The schedule is packed with appointments.

194
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:08,240
It's going to be a busy day.

195
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,840
Understood.

196
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,400
Natsume-san.

197
00:11:13,720 --> 00:11:14,920
What's the goal for today?

198
00:11:15,940 --> 00:11:17,930
Since you're here,

199
00:11:18,630 --> 00:11:20,350
let's aim for the number one spot in sales.

200
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:21,760
You got it.

201
00:11:25,010 --> 00:11:26,100
Good morning!

202
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:27,520
Good morning.

203
00:11:27,780 --> 00:11:28,780
Good morning.

204
00:11:28,880 --> 00:11:29,880
Good morning.

205
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:33,000
Oh, the Twin Princes are both here!

206
00:11:33,290 --> 00:11:34,319
I wanted to see you two together

207
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,130
one last time before the store opened.

208
00:11:36,760 --> 00:11:37,960
It's a great look.

209
00:11:38,260 --> 00:11:39,590
I'm glad I stopped by.

210
00:11:41,950 --> 00:11:44,430
Good luck in Paris, Sahashi-kun.

211
00:11:44,890 --> 00:11:46,940
Thank you very much.

212
00:11:53,020 --> 00:11:54,080
Once we opened,

213
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:57,080
not only did our regulars return
for the "Twin Princes,"

214
00:11:57,520 --> 00:11:59,560
but we had a flood of new customers too.

215
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:01,430
That day,

216
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:03,830
the customers never stopped coming,

217
00:12:04,970 --> 00:12:06,949
and the store was full of smiles.

218
00:12:06,950 --> 00:12:07,770
Thank you for coming today.
Thank you both so much.

219
00:12:08,621 --> 00:12:10,920
- This feels so good.
- It's so cute!

220
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:13,359
Um, if it's okay,

221
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:15,359
could we take a photo together?

222
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:17,680
- Of course.
- Thank you!

223
00:12:20,580 --> 00:12:21,580
Ready?

224
00:12:21,990 --> 00:12:23,390
Okay, smile!

225
00:12:25,500 --> 00:12:28,350
- Thank you!
- Thanks!

226
00:13:24,940 --> 00:13:26,270
I wish

227
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:29,030
this moment could last forever.

228
00:13:40,800 --> 00:13:41,800
Everyone,

229
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:44,190
great work today.

230
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,210
Good work!

231
00:13:49,740 --> 00:13:51,100
You too, Sahashi. Thanks.

232
00:13:52,130 --> 00:13:53,330
Today was so much fun.

233
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:54,900
I agree.

234
00:13:56,840 --> 00:13:58,880
It was definitely worth fighting corporate
for this.

235
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,500
Wait, don't tell me...

236
00:14:03,090 --> 00:14:04,090
Hey!

237
00:14:04,330 --> 00:14:06,089
Should we take a group photo?

238
00:14:06,090 --> 00:14:07,090
I want one!

239
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:08,780
Yeah! Let's do it!

240
00:14:08,960 --> 00:14:10,136
- Definitely!
- Where should we take it?

241
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,169
- Let's just do it right here.
- Here?

242
00:14:11,170 --> 00:14:11,760
Yeah.

243
00:14:12,050 --> 00:14:13,450
Alright, everyone, huddle in.

244
00:14:14,870 --> 00:14:16,550
Sahashi-san, you're standing too far away!

245
00:14:17,180 --> 00:14:18,649
Get in here, come on. Okay!

246
00:14:18,650 --> 00:14:20,850
Alright, say "ROMY"!

247
00:14:23,410 --> 00:14:24,410
Let's see.

248
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:25,990
How is it?

249
00:14:26,370 --> 00:14:27,810
We ended up having the highest sales

250
00:14:28,170 --> 00:14:30,160
out of every ROMY branch that day.

251
00:14:31,160 --> 00:14:34,300
Tanouchi-san told me about it later.

252
00:14:36,800 --> 00:14:37,630
Hey, let's take one more!
One more!

253
00:14:38,361 --> 00:14:39,440
Okay, one more!

254
00:14:43,340 --> 00:14:44,240
Ready?

255
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:45,500
ROMY!

256
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:16,270
Congratulations on hitting the goal,

257
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:17,350
Chief Mamiya.

258
00:15:18,320 --> 00:15:19,320
Yeah.

259
00:15:20,310 --> 00:15:22,320
First place is a huge deal.

260
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,360
It's all thanks to you.

261
00:15:24,790 --> 00:15:25,790
Thank you.

262
00:15:26,160 --> 00:15:27,160
No.

263
00:15:27,390 --> 00:15:30,610
I only pushed myself this hard
because I was with you, Natsume-san.

264
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:33,990
Got your passport?

265
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Is it in there?

266
00:15:35,300 --> 00:15:36,300
It's in there.

267
00:15:36,470 --> 00:15:37,470
And your ticket?

268
00:15:37,910 --> 00:15:38,910
Got that too.

269
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:40,260
Good.

270
00:15:41,620 --> 00:15:44,880
Even though we were only number one
for a single day,

271
00:15:45,990 --> 00:15:47,450
I'm not going to stop there.

272
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:52,390
So, are you going to move to corporate?

273
00:15:53,350 --> 00:15:54,350
Corporate?

274
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:57,990
You've been helping Chief Harada
with the new recruit training.

275
00:15:58,480 --> 00:16:00,960
And you said you were interested
in being an instructor, right?

276
00:16:01,360 --> 00:16:02,360
Oh, that.

277
00:16:02,940 --> 00:16:03,940
Yeah.

278
00:16:04,400 --> 00:16:05,790
But like I said,

279
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:08,290
I still prefer working with customers.

280
00:16:10,040 --> 00:16:11,640
So I'm going to stay on the front lines.

281
00:16:13,340 --> 00:16:14,340
Besides...

282
00:16:17,330 --> 00:16:20,720
I have to be here when you get back.

283
00:16:22,420 --> 00:16:23,420
Wait...

284
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:28,400
I want to stay on the front lines until
I've achieved something I'm proud of.

285
00:16:28,620 --> 00:16:29,820
I'm not done yet.

286
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,030
And next time,

287
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:35,750
we're taking the number one spot
for the whole season.

288
00:16:37,780 --> 00:16:38,780
Natsume-san.

289
00:16:40,930 --> 00:16:41,930
Listen.

290
00:16:42,320 --> 00:16:45,560
I'm going to be so much better that you
won't even recognize me when you get back.

291
00:16:48,660 --> 00:16:49,660
Good.

292
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:11,300
Natsume-san.

293
00:17:12,250 --> 00:17:13,250
Yeah?

294
00:17:42,770 --> 00:17:43,870
You're kind,

295
00:17:45,790 --> 00:17:46,950
and so reliable.

296
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:50,700
You always put others first.

297
00:17:55,910 --> 00:17:58,430
The way you're always there to give me
that cool push forward...

298
00:17:58,890 --> 00:18:00,540
I truly respect you for that.

299
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,610
That part of you

300
00:18:04,630 --> 00:18:06,270
has saved me more times than I can count.

301
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:09,490
From now on,

302
00:18:10,650 --> 00:18:12,890
I'm going to keep finding new reasons
to admire you.

303
00:18:14,470 --> 00:18:19,870
Every single time, I'll think about
how lucky I am to have met you.

304
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:23,400
So,

305
00:18:25,920 --> 00:18:28,420
I'll work hard to be someone
who makes you feel the same way.

306
00:18:31,160 --> 00:18:33,250
Since you make me so happy,

307
00:18:36,040 --> 00:18:37,240
I'm going to work just as hard

308
00:18:38,980 --> 00:18:41,450
to make sure you feel the same way.

309
00:18:48,080 --> 00:18:49,840
We'll be apart for a while,

310
00:18:51,210 --> 00:18:53,050
but I promise I'll never
make you regret this.

311
00:18:54,750 --> 00:18:55,750
Yeah.

312
00:18:56,320 --> 00:18:57,320
So,

313
00:18:59,650 --> 00:19:01,030
from now on,

314
00:19:03,170 --> 00:19:04,680
please stay by my side.

315
00:19:11,380 --> 00:19:12,380
Natsume-san,

316
00:19:15,360 --> 00:19:16,460
I love you so much.

317
00:19:25,780 --> 00:19:26,780
Yeah.

318
00:19:49,840 --> 00:19:51,580
You can be a real pain sometimes,

319
00:19:53,542 --> 00:19:55,442
but you're also incredibly reliable.

320
00:19:57,210 --> 00:19:58,510
I know that better than anyone.

321
00:20:01,950 --> 00:20:02,950
And I know

322
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:08,360
you're always thinking of me.

323
00:20:12,910 --> 00:20:15,070
A lot might happen in the future,

324
00:20:17,580 --> 00:20:19,880
but I know we'll be just fine
as long as we're together.

325
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:39,280
I'm really looking forward to it...

326
00:20:39,610 --> 00:20:40,890
to our life together.

327
00:20:43,170 --> 00:20:44,170
Yeah.

328
00:21:00,560 --> 00:21:01,560
I...

329
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:04,720
I'll be waiting for you.

330
00:21:52,410 --> 00:21:53,410
I'll be right here,

331
00:21:55,130 --> 00:21:57,210
waiting for you to come back
even better than before.

332
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:02,050
I'll be looking forward to it.

333
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,839
It's been six months
since Touma left for Paris.

334
00:22:21,840 --> 00:22:24,659
This one has a richer, creamier texture,

335
00:22:24,660 --> 00:22:25,570
so it's perfect for the upcoming season.

336
00:22:25,640 --> 00:22:27,160
The Yurakucho branch

337
00:22:27,520 --> 00:22:29,510
has even welcomed some new BAs.

338
00:22:32,410 --> 00:22:33,410
Ah!

339
00:22:34,350 --> 00:22:35,350
I'm so sorry.

340
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:37,390
Please forgive me.

341
00:22:41,190 --> 00:22:42,190
It's okay.

342
00:22:42,280 --> 00:22:43,280
Who would've thought

343
00:22:43,710 --> 00:22:45,830
that Hoshina-kun would already
be a senior to someone?

344
00:22:46,200 --> 00:22:48,600
I was just like that when I first started.

345
00:22:51,030 --> 00:22:51,920
What do you think?
As for Touma,

346
00:22:53,200 --> 00:22:54,380
we keep in touch

347
00:22:54,840 --> 00:22:56,730
whenever we have a spare moment.

348
00:22:59,020 --> 00:23:00,620
But Emma-san is working him to the bone,

349
00:23:00,850 --> 00:23:01,979
so every day seems like
a real struggle for him.

350
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:04,149
Touma! Did you check that
look I sent you yesterday?

351
00:23:04,150 --> 00:23:05,150
Yes, I did.

352
00:23:05,280 --> 00:23:09,490
Then why does it look like this?

353
00:23:09,610 --> 00:23:12,890
Based on her bone structure, I thought
this would highlight her features better.

354
00:23:13,170 --> 00:23:14,080
That's why I intentionally kept the blush
a bit more subtle...

355
00:23:14,081 --> 00:23:15,650
You don't understand a thing!

356
00:23:17,390 --> 00:23:18,720
I'm home.

357
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:28,000
(Sahashi Touma: Call me after work)

358
00:23:45,250 --> 00:23:46,250
Good work today.

359
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:48,280
You too.

360
00:23:49,580 --> 00:23:50,940
Aren't you at work right now?

361
00:23:51,690 --> 00:23:52,890
I'm on my break.

362
00:23:53,850 --> 00:23:55,149
Just seeing you for a second

363
00:23:55,150 --> 00:23:56,150
makes me happy.

364
00:23:57,070 --> 00:23:58,070
I see.

365
00:23:58,870 --> 00:23:59,960
Hang in there.

366
00:24:02,130 --> 00:24:03,970
I love it when you tell
me to "hang in there."

367
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:06,750
Touma.

368
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,000
Sorry,

369
00:24:09,190 --> 00:24:10,590
I have to get back.

370
00:24:12,210 --> 00:24:13,360
Alright, Natsume-san.

371
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:16,500
Goodnight.

372
00:24:17,550 --> 00:24:18,550
Goodnight.

373
00:24:43,540 --> 00:24:44,540
Natsume-san.

374
00:24:47,666 --> 00:24:49,006
I'll be back before you know it.
